This paper discusses a traffic engineering scheme for communication networks, specifically focusing on securing the traffic between two core nodes. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and network security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of redundancy to protect against link failures, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT) and reliability engineering (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed scheme to optical and IP networks, which are both subfields of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
